fields.description:
As a user of the Eucalyptus Management Console I would like to create an alarm similar to an existing one via the alarm's details page so that I can easily copy the alarm to other resources.  

Example use case: Apply a CPUUtilization alarm to 3 given instances. 
CloudWatch doesn't support assigning a single alarm to a defined set of instances, despite the boto supporting the following data structure for alarm dimensions:
{code}
{'InstanceId': ['i-one', 'i-two', ...]}
{code}

See the comment thread in EUCA-12185 for notes on the limitations of CloudWatch alarm dimensions.

"Create alarm like this" (a.k.a. copy alarm) aims to offer a streamlined way to copy an alarm to multiple resources.
